Miel 10-Mar-20 10:52 PM
The Romulan walked into the turbolift and turned to face the door, watching it slide closed with barely a sound. She looked up slightly, opening her mouth to speak “Deck…” Sudden palpitations in her heart prevented her from finishing her sentence, and Nira slowly backed away, hand on her chest, until her back hit the metallic wall of the turbolift. Her chest heaved as she tried to breath, the air choking in her throat. She slowly slid down until she was sitting on the floor. All the memories came flooding back to her. The sound of phasers, the flashing lights, the screams. She could not remember if she had been crying or not, and for some reason this bothered her more than it should.. Her fingers clutched at the fabric of her uniform, as if that would help get her heart back in order. Why could it not have ended then and there? Everything would have been so, so much simpler… Years and years of constant paranoia, of fear, of hatred… She was just a child… How could she do the things they blamed her for? She gasped, finally managing to breath, the back of her head resting against the cold metal behind her, beads of sweat dripping down her forehead. Barely a few seconds had passed, but they felt like an eternity. She stood still, not bothering getting up, slowly catching back her breath. The past is the past… Nothing bad can happen. Not now. She closed her eyes, took a deep breath, and held on to the wall as she got back up on shaky legs “Deck.. 5 please..” (edited)

Parlac stepped onto the lift, then turned back to face Blanche and continue talking. "Yes, it is. So, for most people on the ship I am 'Lieutenant Parlac' or 'Lieutenant'. You are welcome to call me 'Parlac' if you like. It would be similar to me calling you Blanche. My given name is Rekat, but that's only used with family or with extremely close friends. The way names are used in Cardassian culture is just as important as everything else about our language-- you might intentionally refer to a close friend or family member by their family name rather than their given name, if you wanted to impart something negative; disappointment, for example, or anger. My family called me 'Parlac' for quite awhile after I joined Starfleet." He winced at the memory. "They've all returned to calling me Rekat now, except for Meros."
